The Paris district where Parisians are priced out
description: In 50 years, the 8th arrondissement of the French capital, home to the Champs-Elysées and the 'Golden Triangle,' has lost nearly half its population. The mass acquisition of real estate by ultra-wealthy foreigners has driven locals out.

description: 'The Studio' broke the record of 11 Emmys for a comedy in a season, set by 'The Bear' in 2024. Every acting winner other than Jean Smart for 'Hacks' was a first timer.

headline: The US-Israeli war against Gaza
description: The United States' fierce campaign against international justice is an implicit admission of its complicity in the crimes committed by Israel in the Gaza Strip, historian Jean-Pierre Filiu argues in his column.

headline: 'Not a job, but a love story': Morocco's racing pigeon craze
description: Unlike Europe, where the number of breeders is declining, Moroccans are embracing pigeon racing with enthusiasm. In Casablanca, more than 1,000 fanciers are concerned about rising temperatures that threaten their birds.

headline: Putin's party prevails in Russian elections even without campaigning
description: Local elections were held across Russia on September 12 and 14. The campaign was particularly dull in Kostroma, a tourist town northeast of Moscow, revealing a society stifled by repression and overcome by apathy and weariness.

headline: Israeli intelligence admits Iran's nuclear program has not been destroyed
description: Israeli officials have recently provided French authorities with their own assessment of the airstrikes that targeted Tehran's nuclear arsenal in June. This information is particularly valuable to France after American intelligence agencies have halted all cooperation with their European partners regarding the Iranian nuclear program.

headline: Undercover but never unmasked: The untold story of a KGB spy in France
description: Following archival research and interviews with witnesses, Le Monde pieced together the completely unknown story of 'Lydia Tows,' a Russian agent who died in Paris in 1999. Working in tandem with a French police officer, she carried out a decades-long infiltration mission with devastating consequences.
